cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI 

The paper deals with text classification using character-level convolutional neural networks with an image-based character encoder. This involves both natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.CL and cs.CV respectively. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with open document classification tasks, which is related to information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI), covered by the sub-categories cs.IR and cs.AI respectively.
